The current code is too convoluted > and thus it is very easy to introduce new bugs. This simplification effort is > the primary motivation behind re-working the `aho-corasick` crate to not only > bundle algorithms like Teddy, but to also provide regex-like match semantics > automatically. > > Moving forward, the plan is to join up with the `bstr` and `regex-automata` > crates, with the former providing more sophisticated substring search > algorithms (thereby deleting existing code in `regex`) and the latter providing > ahead-of-time compiled DFAs for cases where they are inexpensive to compute.
